/target
/.cargo/

# Rust build lockfile — this crate is a library, so we do
# not commit Cargo.lock. See https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/faq.html#why-do-binaries-have-cargolock-in-version-control-but-not-libraries
# This rule also covers `fuzz/Cargo.lock`: the cargo-fuzz harness's
# lockfile is regenerated by every `cargo fuzz build`, so it is kept
# out of version control alongside the library lockfile rather than
# tracked.
Cargo.lock
